<br>
I have a question that I'm hoping someone might be able to answer.<br>
<br>
For those familair with the cleric epic, in BW, Ixiblat Fer is a triggered spawn.  The turn-in mob (whose name completely escapes me at the moment) spawns at 6pm and despawns at 6am each game day.<br>
<br>
My question is this:  Once a cleric completes the turn in, Ixiblat spawns and then is slain, does anyone know if the original turn-in mob will again pop at the next 6pm game cycle, or is there a 'waiting period' that must transpire first?<br>
<br>
If anyone has any information or comments on this matter, they would be greatly appreciated.  My guild is looking into the possiblity that we finish this part of the epic for multiple clerics, but I thought I heard somewhere that the re-spawn of the turn in mob was rather lengthy now, and waiting for it wasn't necessarily feasable anymore.<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for your help and comments.<br>
